===Etymology 2===
{{zh-forms|s=没|t2=没|alt=𣴬,𣳚,歿}}

According to {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}}, formed from the convergence of two etyma:
* {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*mit||to extinguish}}. The ''i'' ~ ''u'' alternation is a common phenomenon in Sino-Tibetan.
* An etymon meaning "to dive", whence {{cog|my|မြုပ်||to sink; to be submerged}}, which is a loan from {{cog|mkh-pro|*(b)ləp||to immerse}} according to {{zh-ref|Shorto (1972)}}.

Unrelated to etymology 1.

